# ───────────────────────── Lure .gitignore ─────────────────────────
# Defensive by design: this is a PUBLIC repo, so anything that could be
# a secret, an internal plan, a draft, or unverifiable media is blocked
# by default. If you truly need to commit one of these, use `git add -f`.

# --- secrets / credentials / env (NEVER commit real ones) ---
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
*.key
*.pem
*.p12
*.pfx
*.crt
id_rsa*
id_ed25519*
secrets.*
credentials.*
*secret*
*credential*
*apikey*
*api_key*
*.token

# --- internal planning / strategy / drafts (keep OUT of public) ---
PLAN.md
*plan*.md
*PLAN*.md
*master-plan*
*masterplan*
*strateg*
*roadmap*
*.draft
*.draft.*
*-draft.*
draft-*
drafts/
*-post.md
*_post.md
NOTES.md
notes.md
notes/
TODO.md
todo.md
internal/
private/
_private/
scratch/
scratchpad/

# --- unverifiable media (screen recordings etc.) ---
# raw video is almost always a capture you don't want auto-shared publicly
*.mp4
*.mov
*.webm

# --- local working data (learning memory / results) ---
brain.json
playbook.local.json
pending.csv
results.csv

# --- os / editor / build ---
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.DS_Store
.venv/
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
.ipynb_checkpoints/
